profile_positions.description:
While in Uganda, I worked with the Partnership Integrated for Human Rights (PIP) as a freelance in Human Rights and protection of human rights defenders living in Bukavu and Uvira from February 2016 to May 2019. Generally, my tasks consisted of:

- Training junior and senior human rights defenders on human rights, monitoring of human rights and international humanitarian law violations, reporting technics, and advocacy;

- Advising the organization on specific cases of human rights defenders under threat and coming up with written practical recommendations;

- Representing the organization at training and any other conferences held by partners in East Africa Community, and producing reports regarding those activities.

Since February 2021, I have been appointed as the focal point of the organization in Europe, the USA, and the Asia zone with a representative mission at the international forum and conference to talk about the organization's activities.

Pieter van Forest offers care, support and treatment to the elderly, amongst them individuals with dementia and poor sight, hearing and speech. As a host(known as a Gentleman) and well-being worker, the following were my tasks: 

• Laying the table before the residents could go to eat, serving thee and/or coffee; this in the morning, afternoon and evening; 

• Having small talk with the residents, doing quizzes, and singing along (as a musician and singer, my skill was effectively used), scrapbooking, walking, bingo, dominoes and board games, etc...

Inter Aid Uganda InterAid Limited is a humanitarian national organization involved in projects geared toward the improvement of livelihoods of the disadvantaged persons both in rural and urban areas. It has consequently a wide experience in the field of developmental assistance, implementing, monitoring and evaluating health, environment, microfinance, and human rights programmes in addition to working with displaced persons, particularly refugees.

As a Community Extension Worker SGBV (Sexual Gender-Based Violence) -Peer Educator, my group focus was the Congolese Refugee Community because I was holding the position of vice president in charge of Administration and finances within. 

The following were my duties:

• Mobilizing and conducting community dialogues with refugees and the host community to raise awareness regarding SGBV (Sexual Gender-Based Violence: Rape, harassment, domestic violence, etc... ) matter;

• Organizing community outreach activities regarding SGBV, redaction, and reporting to the protection officer for further management;

• Conducting interviews with refugee victims of SGBV and making referrals for further management.

DECLIK stands for DEVELOPPER, CONFORTER LES INITIATIVES DES DEFENSEURS DES DROITS HUMAINS AUX KIVU in French. It is a project funded by the European Union to support the work of human defenders in a hostile work environment in the Easter of DR Congo.

• Focal point of Network of protection of human rights defenders, witnesses, and victims (Uvira and Fizi) in partnership with MONUSCO-BCNUDH (Bureau Conjoint des Nations Unies aux Droits de l’Homme), Front Line Defenders, Fonds d'urgence and Protection International.

• Undertake clerical tasks such as data entry, collating, emailing and maintenance of the database

• Support follow-up on cases taken up by Front Line Defenders or other specific projects relating to Human Rights Defenders as requested;

• Draft as requested, minutes, briefings, reports, and appeals;

• Providing training in conflict management and alternative dispute resolution methods to various social groups to promote civil and social peace and justice; training in human rights concepts and their violation as well as, reporting technics and advocating.

• Visiting places of detention and prisons to verify compliance with the law and the proper treatment of detainees according to Geneva Conventions, international human rights instruments, and Congolese criminal procedures; in case of possible human rights violations drafting assessment reports addressed to various partners (e.g., the International Committee of Red Cross, United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs/UNOCHA, United Nations Organization Stabilization Mission in the DRCongo-Penitentiary unit/MONUSCO) and public authorities.

• Monitoring, analyzing, following up, reporting, and advocating for fellow human rights defenders facing threats in Uvira and Fizi, assessing the genuineness of their case before their relocation.

• Carry out administrative tasks as requested;

• Hired trainer in human rights with external partners such as ZOA,  AFPDE, etc...

• Collecting public health data through surveys and interviews; 

 • Reporting to the Head of the Project for analysis; and

 • Contributing to the publication of the final report.
